snippet.textDisplay: I worked at a UPS concord once back in 04-05.  There was so much dust and dirt and soot floating around in the air it looked like that time me and my pyro friend burned medical gloves in a glass bowl in my dad's apartment for like half an hour until we noticed the air was full of carbon soot precipitate and had to clean the entire apartment for about 6 hours until 4am before he got home from work, but in an entire 100000sqf warehouse.  Literally every wall and surface was blackened.  You'd go to the bathroom on your lunch break and scrape the black boogers out of your nose.  One time I asked for extra work after normal hours and they asked me and this other 16 year old looking kid with coke bottle glasses to clean off the overhead plastic that protected the intake line workers from all the dust falling off the overhead conveyor belt.  I asked "Can we have a face mask or goggles?" and they said "..sorry we don't have that" and I said "Okay.. I'm sorry to change my mind but I'm going to say no to doing that, it sounds unsafe to me." And I turned to the other guy and said "I'd recommend you also not do this work because it seems hazardous to me, but do as you like and good luck."  and I went home.  They wanted us to clean it because some high up CEO type guy was coming in the next day.  I was such a good worker that one time they put me in a loading truck for 2 people, alone, during the rush.  This one box wouldnt wedge into the top corner so I stood on the trucks raised conveyor belt and drop kicked the box into the top corner, and fell safely on the hoard of inflowing boxes that I couldn't pack on time.  My scanner was concerned that I fell and yelled to the floor manager to send another GUY in to help me.  I was pissed.
